\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. A. anceps} Mitf.,{\i  Bamboo Garden} 181 (1896). Rhizomes far-creeping. Stems up to 4 m × 15 mm, greenish or brownish, the older ones arching. Stem-sheaths deciduous. Branches numerous at each node. Leaves (5-)7-10(-15) cm × (4-)7-8(-18) mm, linear-lanceolate, with 2-4(-6) veins on each side of the midrib; lower surface pale, concolorous.{\i  Locally naturalized in Britain and the Channel Islands.} [Br Ga.] ({\i W. Himalaya.})
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. A. fastuosa} (Latour-Marliac ex Mitf.) Lehaie,{\i  Bambou} ({\i Mons}) {\b 2}: 215 (1907) ({\i Semiarundinaria fastuosa} (Latour-Marliac ex Mitf.) Makino). Rhizomes shortly creeping. Stems up to 8 m × 40 mm, stiffly erect, very thin-walled, usually terete, but sometimes unilaterally flattened on upper internodes. Stem-sheaths deciduous (rarely over-wintering in a partly decayed condition). Branches several at each node, short, erect, crowded. Leaves 10-20 cm × 15-20(-30) mm, narrowly oblong or lanceolate, long-acuminate, glabrous, with 4-8(-10) pairs of veins on each side of the midrib; lower surface dull green, concolorous.{\i  Locally naturalized in Britain and Ireland}. [Br Hb.] ({\i C. & S. Japan}.)
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 3. A. japonica} Siebold & Zucc. ex Steudel,{\i  Syn. Pl. Glum. }{\b 1}: 334 (1855) ({\i Sasa japonica} (Siebold & Zucc. ex Steudel) Makino, {\i Pseudosasa japonica} (Siebold & Zucc. ex Steudel) Makino). Rhizomes usually very short. Stems up to 7 m × 20 mm, erect, thin-walled, leafless and without branches below; upper nodes each with a single branch. Stem-sheaths long-persistent, rough. Leaves 8-33 cm × (10-)20-40(-55) mm, narrowly lanceolate, long-acuminate, glabrous, with 4-8(-10) veins on each side of midrib; lower surface ¼ green, ¾ more or less glaucous. Oral setae often absent.{\i  Frequently naturalized in W. Europe.} [?Az Br Ga Hb.] ({\i Japan, Korea}.)
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 4. A. simonii} (Carrière) A. & C. Rivière, Bambous 286 (1878) (Pleioblastus simonii (Carrière) Nakai. Rhizomes creeping. Stems up to 7 m × 20 mm, the older ones arching. Stem-sheaths persistent. Branches several at each node. Leaves 5-30 cm × (5-)15-35 mm, narrowly lanceolate, with 4-6(-9) veins on each side of the midrib; lower surface ½ green, ½ more or less glaucous.{\i  Locally naturalized in Britain.} [Br.] ({\i China and Japan}.)
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 5. A. vagans} Gamble, {\i Kew Bull.}{\b  1915}: 350 (1915). Rhizomes far-creeping. Stems up to 1·25 m × 5 mm, slightly zig-zag. Stem-sheaths persistent. Branches 1 at each node. Leaves 12-20 cm × (5-)10-25(-30) mm, narrowly lanceolate, sparsely hairy above, pubescent beneath, with (3-)5-6 veins on each side of the midrib; lower surface concolorous.{\i  Locally naturalized in Britain.} [Br.] ({\i Origin unknown}.)
